parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the secondary air injection system can cause the vehicle to go into limp mode, resulting in a loss of power and speed, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine light and TRAC off light come on
the vehicle loses power and speed
the vehicle goes into limp mode
the vehicle will not exceed a certain speed (e.g. 25mph
35mph
40mph
55mph)
the vehicle has reduced torque and acceleration
the air conditioner may not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can lead to structural failure, compromising the vehicle's safety and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The frame has rusted through in several spots
causing concerns about the vehicle's structural integrity.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal sticks or accelerates on its own
causing the vehicle to move unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the secondary air injection system can cause the vehicle to enter limp mode, reducing power and speed, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on
and the vehicle enters limp mode
reducing power and speed. Error codes P2440
and P2445 are commonly reported.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clock spring can cause the horn to malfunction, which can lead to safety issues in emergency situations.
symptoms: The horn does not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the steering system can cause loss of control, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle's steering system fails
causing the vehicle to wander or lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the plastic foot rest can cause a driving hazard, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The plastic foot rest comes loose and gets tangled up in the driver's feet while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the secondary air injection system can cause the vehicle to go into "limp mode," resulting in reduced power and speed, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Check engine light and TRAC OFF light illumination
loss of power
engine stuttering
and inability to accelerate above 30-40 mph.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The drive train vibration can cause loss of control, accidents, or mechanical failures, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Vibration or shaking of the vehicle during acceleration
particularly in 1st and 2nd gear
and loud whining noise from under the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clutch and transmission issues can cause loss of power, inability to shift gears, and accidents, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and transmission grinding or hesitation to engage gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The acceleration and power loss can cause accidents, particularly when merging onto highways or changing lanes, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle fails to accelerate
loss of power
engine stuttering
and inability to maintain speed.
